<sect1 id="ClearExpireDays">
  <title>ClearExpireDays</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.File.ClearExpireDays<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.File.ClearExpireDays</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>File.ClearExpireDays</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>ClearExpireDays</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis><emphasis>lfn</emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold"></emphasis><emphasis role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>lfn</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>A string containing the logical name of the file.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">ClearExpireDays </emphasis>function clears a
  logical file's expiration criteria (the <emphasis>expireDays</emphasis>
  attribute).</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">A := STD.File.ClearExpireDays('~samples::myscope::myfile');
 //clears a file's expireDays 
</programlisting>

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="GetExpireDays">GetExpireDays</link>, <link
  linkend="SetExpireDays">SetExpireDays</link></para>
</sect1>
